properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 14 at 3:49PM CST until January 15 at 3:00PM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...Winter Weather Advisory is in effect from Midnight tonight
through 3 PM CST Wednesday for two to four inches of snow...

.Snow will develop Wednesday morning across central Minnesota.
Two to four inches of snow is expected for Douglas, Todd,
Morrison, Mille Lacs, and Kanabec counties. Snow will taper off
Wednesday afternoon. Motorists should exercise caution when
traveling and allow for extra time to get to their destination.
Please drive slowly and with caution if roads are slippery.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 4
inches.

* WHERE...Douglas, Todd, Morrison, Mille Lacs and Kanabec
Counties.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to 3 PM CST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning commute. The cold wind
chills as low as 20 below zero could cause frostbite on
exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Motorists should exercise caution when
traveling and allow for extra time to get to their destination.
Please drive slowly and with caution if roads are slippery..
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 3 PM CST WEDNESDAY
